for us or bad? Can we avoid much of the trouble we </div><div class="t m271 xa3 h16 y79e ff3 fsd fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">experience? How? </div><div class="t mb8 x63 h16 ya97 ff3 fsd fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">SUMMARY: Psalm 91 presents in 16 verses a positive attribution of </div><div class="t m21e x63 h16 y94e ff3 fsd fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">faith and confidence in the protection and care of God over His tried </div><div class="t m5ae x63 h16 yb70 ff3 fsd fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">and faithful people. This faith expressed by David and learned by </div><div class="t m6bb x63 h16 y18 ff3 fsd fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Israel&apos;s king through much affliction, is to become an expression of </div><div class="t m6bc x63 h16 ya99 ff3 fsd fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">our faith as we near the time of trouble. We too must learn to trust </div><div class="t m2ef x63 h16 y186 ff3 fsd fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">God more fully and be prepared to live by faith during the disastrous </div><div class="t me1 x63 h16 yb71 ff3 fsd fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">times ahead. The present state of danger in the world is but a breeze </div><div class="t m611 x63 h16 y88b ff3 fsd fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">compared with the storm soon to burst upon men and women every-</div><div class="t m2cb x63 h16 y951 ff3 fsd fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">where. But we are assured: &quot;When you pass through the waters I will </div><div class="t m6bd x63 h16 y18a ff3 fsd fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">be with you; and through the rivers, they shall not overwhelm you; </div><div class="t m6be x63 h16 y18b ff3 fsd fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">when you walk through the fire you shall not be burned, and the </div><div class="t m3ba x63 h16 yb72 ff3 fsd fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">flame shall not consume you&quot; (Isa. 43:2, RSV). </div><div class="t m2cd x63 h16 y120 ff3 fsd fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">100 </div></div><div class="pi" data-data='{"ctm":[1.000000,0.000000,0.000000,1.000000,0.000000,0.000000]}'></div></div>
